node.text: It’s ok to fail, it’s ok to go through hard and trying times, it’s ok that life isn’t perfect. The key is to not stay in the area of funk and doubt. Lift yourself up and keep fighting! What doesn’t kill you will make you stronger! 💪🏽 comment and tag 2 friends!

node.text:
Make sure the moves you make are powerful and purposeful. A lot of times it’s bigger than us. I’m not only trying to inspire the world and lead by example for you all. But I want to inspire my little brother and my family to break generational curses! To show what is possible in life when you practice discipline and work on yourself for the better and gain control of your mind! When you align yourself with God the blessings are Abundant! 🙏🏽 
Proud of my little brother @bronsonzins for working on his growth as well.
📸 @shotbysham

node.text: I Know my pops wasn’t with us in the physical for my wedding day, but he was definitely with us in spirit. I felt him there with me. Our wedding day landed a day in between a tropical storm on Monday and a COVID restriction shut down on Weds! My dad was in heaven pulling some strings with the Lord! Lol thanks pops! 🙏🏽 I am so beyond thankful for my mother always standing right by my side through every step of life with me, for helping me become the man I am today and for loving and welcoming my wife as her own daughter! Im so glad my brother was by my side through it all as well! Love my family to death! Thank you to my Wife @lianev for setting up this beautiful memorial for my dad at our wedding, it meant the world to me, my mom and my brother. 🤍🕊
